-- Indian shares hit near 2-month closing low; Infosys slumps
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 06:07AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 8 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell for a third straight session on Tuesday to their lowest closing level in nearly two months as software stocks slumped after Citigroup downgraded certain companies including Infosys <INFY.NS> ahead of its results on Friday.

Infosys provisionally tumbled 4.7 percent while Tata Consultancy Services <TCS.NS> ended lower 1.6 percent.